724773f.text:
Willett Street, at, adjoining and south of the S. E. corner of Delancey Street, showing structures that are to be demolished as being in the way of the Williamsburg Bridge. Delancey Street is at the left and the view is eastward.
Abouy 1901
Ewing Galloway
1EG ~ 1773
724773f.folder: Willett Street & Delancey Street, Manhattan, NY

719292f-a.text:
Delancey Street, north side, at "illett Street, showing both N.E. and N.V. corners at this point. To the east of the former is a 2 and a half story house (No.234) sandwiched between tenements. These are No'g 232 and 236; the 7 story structure being the first rentioned. At the oppo-aite corner and only partially seen is a 6 story building bearing No's 222-226 Delancey Street and No. 45 'illett Street. The photographer is standing under the Ailliamsburg Bridge approach and is viewing north eastward from Sheriff Street.
April 14, 1928
P.L.Sperr
